value.en-GB: Executive Board of the Technical Centre for Agricultural and Rural Cooperation (CTA), as per decision no 4/2013 of the ACP-EU Committee of Ambassadors of 7 November 2013. Appointed members to the Executive Board of the Technical Centre for Agricultural and Rural Cooperation (CTA), as per decision no 4/2013 of the ACP-EU Committee of Ambassadors of 7 November 2013 on the Statutes of the Centre. For a term of five years, ending on 6 November 2018:* Professor Baba Y. Abubakar* Professor Augusto Manuel Correia* Dr Helena Johansson* Professor Faustin R. Kamuzora* Professor Clement K. SankatFor a term of three years and four months ending on 29 February 2020:* Professor Frederike Praasterink
value.fr-FR: Conseil d'administration du Centre technique de coopération agricole et rurale (CTA), conformément à la décision n ° 4/2013 du Comité des ambassadeurs des pays ACP-UE du 7 novembre 2013. Membres nommés au Conseil d'administration du Centre technique de coopération agricole et rurale (CTA), conformément à la décision n° 4/2013 du Comité des ambassadeurs des pays ACP-UE du 7 Novembre 2013 sur les statuts du Centre. Pour un mandat de cinq ans, se terminant le 6 novembre 2018:* Professeur Baba Y. Abubakar* Professeur Augusto Manuel Correia* Dr Helena Johansson* Professeur Faustin R. Kamuzora* Professeur K. Clement SankatPour un mandat de trois ans et quatre mois, se terminant le 29 février 2020:* Professeur Frederike Partirent

biography.en-GB: PhD in Tropical Agriculture (1990) from the Instituto Superior de Agronomia (Universidade Técnica de Lisboa), Portugal* Associate Professor (Sustainable Development of African Rural Communities, Tropical Agriculture Production and Systems Tropical Agriculture) at the Instituto Superior de Agronomia (ISA) since 1981* Former member of the Steering Committee of the European Forum for Agricultural Research (EFARD) (1999-2001)* Former president of the Portuguese Agency for Development (IPAD) (2005-2012)* National Expert for the 5th Framework Program for Development Assistance of the EU
biography.fr-FR: Doctorat d’agriculture tropicale (1990), Instituto Superior de Agronomia (Universidade Técnica de Lisboa), Portugal* Professeur associé (Développement durable des communautés rurales africaines, agriculture tropicale et systèmes de agricoles tropicaux), Instituto Superior de Agronomia, depuis 1981* Membre du comité du Forum européen sur la recherche agricole pour le développement (EFARD) de 1999 à 2001* Président de l’Agence portugaise de développement (IPAD) de 2005 à 2012* Expert national du 5e programme-cadre pour l'aide publique au développement de l'Union européenne

biography.en-GB: PhD from the University of Guelph’s School of Engineering, Canada, Honorary Doctorate degree (2010) from the University of New Brunswick MSc and BSc in Mechanical Engineering from the University of the West Indies, Trinidad and Tobago. Chartered Engineer (CEng), Fellow of the Institute of Agricultural Engineers (FIAgrE) of the UK, Fellow of the Association of Professional Engineers of Trinidad and Tobago (FAPETT) and Fellow of the Canadian Society for Bioengineering* President of the University of Belize since 2017* Board of Advisors, Confucius Institute, Hanban, Beijing, China* Former Pro-Vice-Chancellor and Campus Principal of The University of the West Indies, St Augustine Campus, Trinidad (2008-2016)
biography.fr-FR: Doctorat d’ingénierie, University of Guelph’s School of Engineering, Canada Doctorat honorifique (2010, University of New Brunswick, Canada Maîtrise universitaire ès sciences et licence en Ingénierie mécanique, University of the West Indies, Trinidad et Tobago* Président, University of Belize, depuis 2017* Membre du conseil d’administration, Confucius Institute, Hanban, Pékin, Chine* Vice-chancelier, The University of the West Indies, St Augustine, Trinidad et Tobago, de 2008 à 2016

biography.en-GB: PhD in Animal Breeding and Genetics (1985) from Cornell University, USA* Visiting Professor, University of Abuja (2016-present)* Pioneer Executive Secretary, Agricultural Research Council of Nigeria (2006-2016)* Director, Office of the Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Nigeria (2003-2006)* Programme Leader (Poultry), National Animal Production Research Institute (NAPRI/ABU), Shika-Zaria (1991-1997)* Research Officer, NAPRI/ABU (1978-2003)* Promoted Professor of Animal Science, NAPRI/ABU (1995)* Liaison officer, Centre for Agricultural Biosciences International (CABI), (2008- 2016)* Member of the Consultative Group on International Agricultural Research [CGIAR] ExCo & Fund/System Council representing Sub-Saharan Africa, 2008-2009 & 2010-2016 respectively* Chairman, Governing Board of the West and Central African Council for Agricultural Research and Development (CORAF /WECARD), (2010-2012)* Member of the Governing Board of the Forum for Agricultural Research in Africa (FARA), (2010- 2012)* Member of the Expert Panel on the development of Science Agenda for Agriculture in Africa (2013)* Member, Board of Trustees, WorldFish Center (2017-2020)* Received Presidential National Honours Award of Officer of the Order of the Federal Republic (OFR) in 2011 and the CORAF/WECARD Award of Honour for invaluable contribution to Agricultural Research and Development in West and Central Africa in 2012.
biography.fr-FR: Doctorat en Sciences animales et génétique (1985), Cornell University, Etats-Unis* Professeur invité, University of Abuja, depuis 2016* Secrétaire exécutif, Agricultural Research Council of Nigeria, de 2006 à 2016* Directeur du Secrétariat du gouvernement fédéral du Nigéria, de 2003 à 2006* Chef de programme (Volaille), National Animal Production Research Institute (NAPRI/ABU), Nigeria, de 1991 à 1997* Chargé de recherche, NAPRI/ABU, de 1978 à 2003* Professeur des Sciences animales, NAPRI/ABU, 1995* Officier de liaison, Centre for Agricultural Biosciences International (CABI), de 2008 à 2016* Membre, pour le Groupe consultatif pour la recherche agricole internationale (CGIAR), du comité exécutif pour l’Afrique sub-saharienne, de 2008 à 2009, puis de 2010 à 2016* Président du conseil d’administration du Conseil ouest et centre africain pour la recherche et le développement agricoles (CORAF /WECARD), de 2010 à 2012* Membre du conseil d’administration du Forum pour la recherche agricole en Afrique (FARA), de 2010 à 2012* Membre du panel d’experts pour l’Agenda scientifique pour l’agriculture en Afrique (2013)* Membre du conseil d’administration de WorldFish Center, depuis 2017* Received Presidential National Honours Award of Officer of the Order of the Federal Republic (OFR) in 2011 and the CORAF/WECARD Award of Honour for invaluable contribution to Agricultural Research and Development in West and Central Africa in 2012.

biography.en-GB: PhD in Economics (2003) from Lund University, Sweden* Director of the AgriFood Economics Centre, Lund University, Sweden since 2009* Researcher at the Swedish Institute for Food and Agriculture Economics (2001-2008)* Lecturer at the Department of Economics, Lund University (2002-2003)
biography.fr-FR: Doctorat d’Economie (2003), Lund University, Suède* Directrice du AgriFood Economics Centre, Lund University, depuis 2009* Chercheuse au Swedish Institute for Food and Agriculture Economics, de 2001 à 2008* Maître de conference (Economie), Lund University, de 2002 à 2003

biography.en-GB: PhD in Information Technology (2006) from the University of Bradford, USA MSc in Agricultural International Trade (1996) from the North Carolina Agricultural and Technical State University, USA* Permanent Secretary of Tanzanian Ministry of Communication, Science and Technology* Deputy vice-chancellor, Mzumbe University, Tanzania (2007- present)* Researcher and trainer at Mzumbe University (1992 – present)* Executive Secretary of the Agricultural Economist Society of Tanzania
biography.fr-FR: Doctorat de Technologie de l’information (2006), University of Bradford, Etats-Unis Maîtrise universitaire ès sciences de Commerce agricole international (1996), North Carolina Agricultural and Technical State University, Etats-Unis* Secrétaire permanent du ministère du ministère de la Communication, des sciences et la technologie de Tanzanie* Vice-chancelier, Mzumbe University, Tanzania, depuis 2007* Chercheur et formateur, Mzumbe University, depuis 1992* Secrétaire exécutif des économistes agricoles de Tanzanie

biography.en-GB: MSc in Horticulture & Crop protection (1988) from Wageningen University & Research, The Netherlands* Senior lecturer (Future Food Systems) at HAS University of Applied Sciences, The Netherlands, since 2006* Expert/Consultant for the FAO (1995-2008)
biography.fr-FR: Maîtrise universitaire ès sciences Horticulture et protection des cultures, Wageningen University & Research, Pays-Bas* Maître de conference (Systèmes alimentaires), HAS University of Applied Sciences, Pays-Bas, depuis 2006* Expert consultante pour la FAO, de 1995 à 2008
